# Frame Budget Standards

This document defines frame time budgets, profiling methodology, and optimization priorities for real-time games.

---

## Budget Definition

### 60 FPS Target

| Platform | Target FPS | Budget (ms) | Notes |
|----------|------------|-------------|-------|
| PC (high) | 60 | 16.67 | Primary target |
| PC (low) | 30 | 33.33 | Minimum spec |
| Console | 60 | 16.67 | Locked or variable |
| Mobile | 30 | 33.33 | Battery, thermal |

### Budget Allocation (16.67ms @ 60fps)

| Category | Allocation | Notes |
|----------|------------|-------|
| Game logic | 4-6 ms | AI, physics, input |
| Rendering (CPU) | 2-4 ms | Culling, batching, submit |
| Rendering (GPU) | 6-10 ms | Draw, post-process |
| Audio | 0.5-1 ms | Mixing, spatial |
| Overhead | 1-2 ms | OS, driver, buffer swap |

