## Frame Pacing

### V-Sync

- [ ] V-sync on for shipping (no tearing)
- [ ] Triple buffering if double-buffer causes stutter
- [ ] Allow disable for benchmarking (uncapped)

### Variable Refresh (G-Sync, FreeSync)

- [ ] Support when available
- [ ] Frame rate can vary; budget still applies to average
- [ ] Avoid sudden large frame time jumps

### Frame Pacing Checklist

- [ ] No frame time spikes from loading or GC
- [ ] Consistent frame times preferred over high average
- [ ] Input latency considered (vsync adds ~1 frame)
- [ ] Frame rate limiter option for power saving (e.g., 30fps cap on mobile)

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Frame budget defined per platform
- [ ] Budget allocation documented
- [ ] Profiling tools and process established
- [ ] CPU vs GPU bound identified
- [ ] Optimization priorities by impact/effort
- [ ] Frame pacing and vsync strategy defined
- [ ] P99 frame time under budget
